-- Darryl Sutter Replaced by Jay Feaster as General Manager of Calgary Flames
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2010-12-28T20:24:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-28/darryl-sutter-replaced-by-jay-feaster-as-general-manager-of-calgary-flames.html
Darryl Sutter  stepped down as
general manager of the Calgary Flames and was replaced by  Jay Feaster , the National Hockey League team said in a statement on
its website.  The Flames are fourth in the Northwest Division with 35
points.  Sutter spent eight seasons with the Flames. Feaster joined
the franchise in July. He won a Stanley Cup as general manager
of the Tampa Bay Lightning in 2004.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  